Ogulagha oil and gas producing communities forum have asked President Muhammadu Buhari to pay host communities 13 percent derivation fund directly. Chairman of the forum, Elder Timi Johnson in a statement said several trillions of naira allocated to the region/oil producing  communities in the name of 13% derivation funds ends up in private pockets . He further explained that It is illegal and unconstitutional to pay the 13% derivation fund which is first line charge through State Governors third line charge on the Federation Account, according to Section 162 (2) of the 1999 constitution as amended. He said this  position of the constitution made it very clear that 13% derivation fund is provided constitutionally and exclusively for the oil/gas producing communities primarily, as compensation for loss of fishing rights and productive Farmlands as a result of oil/gas exploration and production activities. He said “we the leadership of the above named peace loving organization Congratulate Your Excellency, President Muhammadu Buhari for your purposeful leadership and your administration desire to tackled the multi-dimensional syndrome of corruption that has been deviled our dear nation. “It may interest your excellency to know that  the several trillions of naira allocated to our region/oil producing  communities in the name of 13% derivation funds ends up in private pockets while actual oil/gas  producing communities are living in abject poverty  and penury. “Ogulagha Kingdom in Burutu Local Government  Area  of Delta State is host to the following very sensitive national oil /gas installations, Focados Terminal,Focados Estuary ,Focados North Bank, Sokobolo flow station and Yokri flow station, with a combine production capacity  of  over two hundred thousand barrel per day “Your excellency sir, as the father of the nation, we are saddened that with this huge production there is nothing tangible in terms of infrastructural facilities, human capital development and even social amenities such as Higher  Institution , motorable roads,  electricity, good pipe borne water and good health facilities to compensate  for our petro dollar contribution to the national economic growth. “It is on this note that we are  compelled to make the following demands: Henceforth all monies due to our kingdom from the payment of 13% derivation funds should henceforth be channeled  to us through the proposed Presidential Derivation Committee (PDC) and State Implementation Committee (SIC) “We hold heartedly support  your  administration independence financial allocation to the 774 Local Government Council in Nigeria and the state houses of Assembly/Judiciary, we see this as a bold step in the right direction capable of putting a stop to the huge financial irregularities and outright embezzlement of funds meant for those government institutions. “We are happy that allocating 13% derivation funds through the Proposed Presidential Derivation Committee (PDC) and States Implementation Committee (SIC) will put a paid to the multitrillion naira frauds that has occurred in the regime of the funds allocations that has resulted in wastage of over 44 trillion naira. “As leaders of our community  we believe that his excellency  will use his fatherly position to direct  the relevant government  agencies  to do the needful as refusing to do same  will compelled  our people to apply self-help,” he added. 